II 21, 20 materiam rhetorices esse omnes res ad

These passages can leave no reasonable doubt 'that ⁶ ad dicendum ' is out of place by the side of ⁶ oratori,’ a view confirmed by the variants in our Mss.: subiecta ad dicendum —ad dicendum subiecta, which unmistakably point to an interlinear gloss which subsequently came into the text in different places. The phrase was evidently taken from c. 37 29 ‘ut uberem ad dicendum materiam oratores haberent,’ where it is quite appropriate, not to say essential to the context.-As est is here part of the verb, its emphatic position before enim is unjustifiable.
